<span class="header1">TECHNOLOGY SERVICE</span>
<p>The occupations in this field combine an interest in technology
and industry.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Human Resources Manager
</span><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/FG/43222.jpg"
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Industrial Labor Relations
Specialist" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>In an effort to enhance morale and productivity,
limit job turnover, and help organizations increase performance and
improve business results, human resources managers help their firms
effectively use employee skills, provide training and development
opportunities to improve those skills, and increase employees'
satisfaction with their jobs and working conditions. </blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>Many colleges and universities have programs
leading to a bachelor's degree in personnel, human resources, or labor
relations. Some offer degree programs in human resources
administration or human resources management, training and
development, or compensation and benefits.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of human resources
managers was $116,720 in May 2019. </blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Civil Engineer</span><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/FG/43243.jpg"
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Civil Engineer" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>The word "civil" describes anything that has to
do with a city. A civil engineer plans and builds structures that
make our lives easier. As a civil engineer, you would plan and
oversee the building of roads, bridges, and airports. You would also
make sure that these structures were safe to use.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>A bachelor's degree in engineering is needed for
almost all entry-level engineering jobs. A civil engineer must get a
license from the state to offer services directly to the public. A
license requires four years of relevant work experience and passing
an exam. Beginning engineers often work under an experienced
engineer to get their required work experience. A master's degree may 
be needed to be a candidate for promotions. </blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of civil engineers was
$87,060 in May 2019. </blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Fitness Worker</span><br />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>Fitness workers lead, instruct, and motivate
individuals or groups in exercise activities including
cardiovascular exercise, strength training, and stretching. They
work in health clubs, country clubs, hospitals, universities, yoga
and Pilates studios, resorts, and clients' homes.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>An increasing number of employers require
fitness workers to have a bachelor's degree in a field related to
health or fitness such as exercise science or physical education.
Becoming certified by one of the top certification organizations is
increasingly important, especially for personal trainers. One way to
ensure that a certifying organization is reputable is to see that it
is accredited by the National Commission for Certifying Agencies.
</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of fitness workers was
$40,390 in May 2019. </blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Computer Support
Specialist</span><br />
		<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>Computer support specialists provide technical
assistance, support, and advice to customers and other users. This
occupational group includes technical support specialists and 
help-desk technicians. These troubleshooters interpret problems and
provide technical support for hardware, software, and systems. They
answer telephone calls, analyze problems by using automated
diagnostic programs, and resolve recurring
difficulties.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>Training requirements for computer support
specialist positions vary, but many employers prefer to hire
applicants with some formal college education. A bachelor's degree
in computer science or information systems is a prerequisite for
some jobs; other jobs, however, may require only a computer-related
associate degree. And for some jobs, relevant computer experience
and certifications may substitute for formal education. </blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of computer support
specialists was $54,760 in May 2019. </blockquote>

